<answer>The top-rated car rental company in London is Europcar and in Paris is Sixt. The best-rated restaurant in London is Gordon Ramsay at the London House (120 euros per meal) and in Paris is Septime (150 euros per meal). The best-rated hotel in London is The Ritz London (5600 euros per night) and in Paris is Shangri-La Hotel (5200 euros per night).

Assuming you both stay in the same room, the total cost for accommodation will be:
London: 2 nights * 5600 euros/night = 11200 euros
Paris: 3 nights * 5200 euros/night = 15600 euros
Total accommodation cost: 11200 + 15600 = 26800 euros

For meals (2 per day):
London: 2 days * 2 meals/day * 120 euros/meal = 480 euros
Paris: 3 days * 2 meals/day * 150 euros/meal = 900 euros
Total meal cost: 480 + 900 = 1380 euros

The total maximum expense for the 5-day trip will be:
26800 (accommodation) + 1380 (meals) = 28180 euros</answer>
